main event: An object resembling a moving star was observed in Washington, D.C. on November 6, 1961.
interesting points: The object moved at a fast speed in relation to the area., The object made a right turn of 45 degrees., The sighting lasted approximately 5 to 10 minutes., The object was reported to the Air Force from a student near American University., The observation was conducted visually at night while the sky was clear.
sighted object: an object like a moving star
